CHICKENS, GARDENS, AND SURVIVAL AFTER THE CRASH 

Even the once great varieties of Chickens that were available, that would reproduce themselves, 
are gone. Yes chickens will not reproduce or set on their own eggs any more, because selfish men 
have thought they could improve on one of God`s creations by hatching them in Automatic Brooders. At 
the egg farms that produce the eggs for the commercial hatcheries, when the hens get broody they Kill 
her. The reason for this is a broody hen naturally stops laying eggs for a few months and produces no 
income. In three of four generations of killing any chicken with the natural instin to get broody and sit 
on their own eggs, hatch them then raise and prote her young is gone forever. Therefore we have 
chickens all over America, which will no longer reproduce as God ordained for them to. The only breed 
that will still some times reproduce is some of the small Cochin Bantams. 

